I"d<p>Recently I bought a new Raspberry Pi 3 and wanted to run a few Node.js applications on it. Unfortunately the Node.js version that is available on <a href="https://www.raspbian.org/">Raspbian</a> is quite old.</p>

<p>Don’t worry, it’s easy to install. Follow the instructions below and you’re all set.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get update
<span class="nv">$ </span>curl <span class="nt">-sL</span> https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_7.x | <span class="nb">sudo </span>bash -
<span class="nv">$ </span>apt-get <span class="nb">install </span>nodejs
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Verify the installation with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">node -v</code>. It should output something like <em>v7.0.0</em></p>
:ET